                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13065515" author="gagravarr" created="Thu, 14 Jul 2011 21:24:30 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;They should be supported for detection already&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For metadata or content extraction, I&apos;m not aware of any libraries under a suitable license (but I could be wrong!). These would therefore need to be third party external plugins. Or, we&apos;d need to write our own library based on the specs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13065912" author="vivianli" created="Fri, 15 Jul 2011 14:17:23 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Nick,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do you mean TIKA can detect Creative Suite formats already? All I need right now is the content type and version. If they are there, can you let me know how to get the info (a code snippet will be very much appreciated.)?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Vivian&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13065916" author="gagravarr" created="Fri, 15 Jul 2011 14:24:41 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;You may need to be using a recent nightly build / svn build (I can&apos;t remember when it went in), but the regular detection code will (when given a filename) correctly identify the creative suite files. There&apos;s no mime magic for them though&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13066034" author="vivianli" created="Fri, 15 Jul 2011 16:54:04 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you please let me know where I can find the nightly builds? Thanks.&lt;br/&gt;
Also when you said &quot;when given a file name&quot;, did you mean that the detection was purely from the file extension?&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13067360" author="gagravarr" created="Mon, 18 Jul 2011 23:37:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Currently, yes, detection of these types is only done by filename. If someone is able to identify the magic byte patterns for them, then that can be changed!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13068395" author="vivianli" created="Wed, 20 Jul 2011 15:17:14 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Nick. File extension is not what I am looking for.  How soon do you think TIKA will be able to provide metadata for Creative suite formats? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13068409" author="gagravarr" created="Wed, 20 Jul 2011 15:39:43 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Mime magic detection should be quite quick, once someone tracks down some documentation on the file header, or failing that stares at hex dumps of lots of files to crack it&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As for metadata, support will be added a few days after someone submits a patch for it &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.adobe.com/devnet-apps/photoshop/fileformatashtml/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.adobe.com/devnet-apps/photoshop/fileformatashtml/&lt;/a&gt; looks a good place to start for photoshop&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alternately there is a LGPL java library for PSD files (which can&apos;t be included in Tika for license reasons), which could be used as a third party plugin&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13068420" author="vivianli" created="Wed, 20 Jul 2011 15:57:24 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you let me know where to find that java library (with LGPL license)? Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13122934" author="gagravarr" created="Fri, 7 Oct 2011 17:33:42 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;ImageParser currently claims to support image/x-psd, which I believe is incorrect. I suspect we should remove this&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking at &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.adobe.com/devnet-apps/photoshop/fileformatashtml/PhotoshopFileFormats.htm#50577409_pgfId-1055726&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.adobe.com/devnet-apps/photoshop/fileformatashtml/PhotoshopFileFormats.htm#50577409_pgfId-1055726&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://code.google.com/p/java-psd-library/wiki/PsdFileFormat&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://code.google.com/p/java-psd-library/wiki/PsdFileFormat&lt;/a&gt; it should be very quick quick to add support for getting the width, height, depth etc&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13123181" author="gagravarr" created="Fri, 7 Oct 2011 21:53:19 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve added a basic metadata extracting parser in r1180230.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tests and features are based on a simple PSD file of the Apache logo, which was the only PSD file I had to hand. It&apos;d be great if we could get a better sample file, which includes descriptions and EXIF metadata, which we could use to expand the test and probably get a few more bits of metadata from&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13166017" author="damonrand" created="Fri, 9 Dec 2011 10:03:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m attaching a sample PSD file where I have filled dummy data into many of the fields through the Photoshop File Info screen. Also attaching an export of the xmp metadata for this file. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hope this helps. I will do the same for Illustrator shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13167368" author="gagravarr" created="Mon, 12 Dec 2011 05:57:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the test file. Alas the parser doesn&apos;t currently support the file, so first we&apos;ll need to sort then, then we can use it to test and expand the metadata extraction coverage&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13172223" author="amandaluniz" created="Mon, 19 Dec 2011 12:16:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching an InDesign document with dummy metadata.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13172775" author="gagravarr" created="Tue, 20 Dec 2011 00:23:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Adei - any chance you could create a much smaller sample InDesign file (that one is quite large for a test file), and attach it to the InDesign issue (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-291&quot; title=&quot;Adobe InDesign support&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;TIKA-291&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;TIKA-291&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) instead?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13491725" author="tharper" created="Tue, 6 Nov 2012 19:14:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve added a simple InDesign file to (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-291&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-291&lt;/a&gt;) as requested. I know it&apos;s late, but I remain hopeful.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14360344" author="cdedels" created="Fri, 13 Mar 2015 13:37:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I looked at my magic file for Adobe InDesign and found the the first four bytes of the file should be 0x0606edf5 (big endian).  Hope this helps.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14360369" author="gagravarr" created="Fri, 13 Mar 2015 13:50:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=cdedels&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;cdedels&quot;&gt;Christopher Dedels&lt;/a&gt; We already have a more specific InDesign magic added - 0x0606edf5d81d46e5bd31efe7fe74b71d - does that cover your file as well?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At this point, I think we&apos;re hopefully covered for mime magic, the next step is for people to pick a format that interests them and start working on parsers!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14360487" author="cdedels" created="Fri, 13 Mar 2015 15:15:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, that magic matches all the InDesign files I looked at.  Thanks for the info!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14510967" author="ahmedowian" created="Fri, 24 Apr 2015 13:44:11 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;When attempting to scan the bytestream to find the xmp packets, we encountered custom control chars which were invalid xml. Therefore, we opted to use exiftool to parse the xmp, and we took it from there. See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.alfresco.com/jira/browse/MM-371&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.alfresco.com/jira/browse/MM-371&lt;/a&gt; for details.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14512131" author="gagravarr" created="Sat, 25 Apr 2015 02:01:53 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ahmedowian&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ahmedowian&quot;&gt;Ahmed Owian&lt;/a&gt; I&apos;m getting a permission error trying to view that Alfresco JIRA, any chance you could make that JIRA world readable, or replace it with an alternate public URL with the details in?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
